# Local-only env. Never commit; never package.
#
# Files merge convention (matches BXM/UJM):
#   The "Default Values" section is overwritten on every `npx mgr setup`.
#   The "Custom Values" section is preserved verbatim — put your secrets there.
#   Existing values for keys that appear in both sections stay in their original section.
#   Values are normalized to double-quoted form on every merge (handles spaces / special chars).

# ========== Default Values ==========

# ─── GitHub ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GH_TOKEN=""

# ─── Backend Manager ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BACKEND_MANAGER_KEY=""

# ─── macOS signing + notarization ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Point CSC_LINK at build/certs/developer-id-application.p12 (per-brand cert file).
# See docs/signing.md or build/certs/README.md for full setup.
CSC_LINK=""
CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=""

# Notarization (App Store Connect API key)
APPLE_API_KEY=""
APPLE_API_KEY_ID=""
APPLE_API_ISSUER=""
APPLE_TEAM_ID=""

# ─── Windows signing ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Strategy: self-hosted (default) | cloud | local. Overrides config.signing.windows.strategy.
#   self-hosted — Windows signing job runs on a self-hosted runner (e.g. ITW's runner box).
#                 You don't set WIN_EV_TOKEN_PATH / WIN_CSC_KEY_PASSWORD / SIGNTOOL_PATH here;
#                 they live on the runner machine itself.
#   cloud       — Windows signing dispatches to a cloud provider (Azure / SSL.com / DigiCert).
#                 Set WIN_CLOUD_SIGN_PROVIDER + the provider's creds in Custom Values below.
#   local       — Skip CI signing; you sign locally via `npx mgr sign-windows` on your own
#                 Windows box. Same env-var contract as the self-hosted runner.
EM_WIN_SIGN_STRATEGY=""

# Cloud-signing provider (only when EM_WIN_SIGN_STRATEGY=cloud).
WIN_CLOUD_SIGN_PROVIDER=""

# ========== Custom Values ==========

# Anything below this line is yours and won't be touched by `npx mgr setup`.
